Subject: =?UTF-8?q?feat(slayzone):=20in-pane=20window.open=20/=20target=3D?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=5Fblank=20=E2=86=92=20adopt=20as=20a=20pane=20tab?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A page in a browser pane that opens a new window/tab (window.open, target=_blank,
Cmd+click) previously created a lost background tab in the task's windowless
Browser. The host now observes each task Browser's TabStripModel: a tab it did
NOT create (guarded via creating_owned_tab_ around our own AddAndReturnTabAt) is
adopted — minted a view_id + Entry — and surfaced to the renderer via a new
OnNewView(task_id, view_id, url) observer event. The renderer opens a browser tab
bound to that EXISTING view via a new AttachView(view_id, bounds) (composites it
without minting/loading a fresh tab). The TabStripModelObserver base auto-cleans
its observation when a model is destroyed.

NEW_TAB dispositions only — sized window.open popups (NEW_POPUP, e.g. OAuth) open
a separate Browser and are a follow-on phase.
